label.value: branching involved in labyrinthine layer morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branches of the fetal placental villi are generated and organized. The villous part of the placenta is called the labyrinth layer.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a trophoblast cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell of the placental labyrinthine layer.

label.value: epithelial cell morphogenesis involved in placental branching

value.value: The change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when a trophoblast cell elongates to contribute to the branching of the placenta.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in placenta development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another.
The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure.
The process in which the ureteric bud is generated and organized.

The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the ureteric bud from the Wolffian duct. This process begins when the bud protrudes from the duct and ends when it is a recognizable bud.
The developmental growth in which the ureteric bud grows along its axis beginning with the growth of the primary ureteric bud and ending when the branches of the bud have elongated.

label.value: dichotomous subdivision of terminal units involved in ureteric bud branching

value.value: The process in which a ureteric bud bifurcates at its end.

label.value: trifid subdivision of terminal units involved in ureteric bud branching

value.value: The process in which a ureteric bud splits into three units at its end.

label.value: lateral sprouting involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a branch forms along the side of a ureteric bud.

label.value: branch elongation involved in ureteric bud branching

value.value: The growth of a branch of the ureteric bud along its axis.
The process in which the primary ureteric bud grows along its axis dorsally toward the metanephric blastema.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis by epithelial-mesenchymal signaling

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of salivary gland branching as a result of the transfer of information from the epithelial cells to the mesenchymal cells of the salivary gland.
Any process that results in the transfer of information from an epithelial cell to a mesenchymal cell where it is interpreted.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of prostatic bud formation, the morphogenetic process in which a region of the fetal urogenital sinus epithelium is specified to become the prostate, resulting in prostate bud outgrowth.

label.value: negative regulation of prostatic bud formation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of prostatic bud formation, the morphogenetic process in which a region of the fetal urogenital sinus epithelium is specified to become the prostate, resulting in prostate bud outgrowth.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in prostate gland morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of prostate gland branching, the process in which the branching structure of the prostate gland is generated and organized. A branch is a division or offshoot from a main stem.

label.value: regulation of morphogenesis of a branching structure

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of branches are generated and organized.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells of the salivary gland.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of an epithelial cell of the salivary gland.

label.value: epithelial cell maturation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an epithelial cell of the salivary gland to attain its fully functional state.

label.value: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell of the salivary gland. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching morphogenesis in the salivary gland epithelium.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cholesterol transporter activity.

label.value: negative regulation of cholesterol transporter activity

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cholesterol transporter activity.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

label.value: positive regulation of phospholipid catabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of phospholipid catabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phospholipids, any lipid containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.
Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of endoribonuclease.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within ribonucleic acid by creating internal breaks.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of ribonuclease activity, catalysis of the hydrolysis of phosphodiester bonds in chains of RNA.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of ribonuclease activity, catalysis of the hydrolysis of phosphodiester bonds in chains of RNA.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within ribonucleic acid by creating internal breaks.
Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of deoxyribonuclease.

label.value: acinar cell differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize an acinar cell of the salivary gland. Acinar cells are protein-secreting cells in the gland.

label.value: neuron differentiation involved in salivary gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the neurons of the salivary gland.

label.value: cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of the embryonic placenta.

The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a trophoblast giant cell of the placenta. Trophoblast giant cells are the cell of the placenta that line the maternal decidua.
The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell of the ectoplacental cone acquires specialized features of a spongiotrophoblast of the placenta. A spongiotrophoblast cell is a basophilic cell.

label.value: glycogen cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a glycogen cell of the placenta. A glycogen cell is a vacuolated glycogen-rich cell that appears in compact cell islets of the spongiotrophoblast layer.
The cell-cell adhesion process in which the cells of the chorion fuse to the cells of the allantois.
The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta progresses, from its formation to its mature state.
The process in which the spongiotrophoblast layer of the placenta progresses from its formation to its mature state.
The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta is generated and organized.
The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta.

label.value: syncytiotrophoblast cell differentiation involved in labyrinthine layer development

value.value: The process in which a chorionic trophoblast cell acquires specialized features of a syncytiotrophoblast of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The embryonic vessels grow through the layer to come in close contact with the maternal blood supply.

The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a chorion from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure. The chorion is an extraembryonic membrane.

The process in which relatively unspecialized cells of the ectoplacental cone acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chorionic trophoblast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.
